com.usc.bill.dto

Class StudentRecord

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.usc.bill.dto.StudentRecord

  • public class StudentRecord
extends java.lang.Object
    A studentRecord is a a complex structure containing information about and associated with a student. This includes simple demographic information, such as name and address, but also a series of values and flags used to compute a students bill, such as what college the student is attending, whether they have a scholarship, or are active duty military. Additionally the student profile contains a list of courses being taken by the student and a list of transactions, i.e. payments and charges, associated with the student's record.
    Version:
    1.0 11/19/2017
    Author:
    WU, Alamri, STROUD

    • Field Detail

      • activeDuty

        private boolean activeDuty
        activeDuty is a Boolean flag indicating if the student is currently serving on active duty in the US Military. Being activeDuty entitles the student to certain reductions in tuition but limit options with reguard to studying abroad.

      • addressCity

        private java.lang.String addressCity
        The city portion of the address associated with the student, e.g. "Columbia", "Atlanta", "New York City", etc.

      • addressPostalCode

        private java.lang.String addressPostalCode
        The ZIP or postal code associated with the student, e.g. 29170, 10026, 60619.

      • addressState

        private java.lang.String addressState
        The state portion of the address associated with the student, e.g. "SC", "GA", "NY", etc.

      • addressStreet

        private java.lang.String addressStreet
        The street portion of the address associated with the student, e.g. "123 Maple St."

      • balance

        private java.math.BigDecimal balance
        balance is an amount of how much student is owed to the school and vice-verse

      • capstoneEnrolled

        private Term capstoneEnrolled
        capstoneEnrolled is the term, e.g. Spring-2017, when the student first entered the Capstone Program.

      • classStatus

        private java.lang.String classStatus
        The classStatus is the year or class of the student, e.g. Freshman, Sophomore, etc. The value will be translated to the enumerated type ClassStatus and will be restricted as such.

      • college

        private java.lang.String college
        The college is the school which the student is attending. The value of college will be translated to a value of the enumerated type College and be restricted as such.

      • courses

        private java.util.List<Course> courses
        courses is the list of Course objects, i.e. academic classes, associated with the student.

      • emailAddress

        private java.lang.String emailAddress
        The email address associated to the student.

      • firstName

        private java.lang.String firstName
        The first name of the student. E.g. if the student's name is "John Doe" the first name is "John".

      • freeTuition

        private boolean freeTuition
        freeTution is a Boolean flag indicating if all tuition charges are waived for this student.

      • gradAssistant

        private boolean gradAssistant
        gradAssistant is a Boolean flag to indicate if the student is a graduate assistant for the school

      • id

        private java.lang.String id
        The unique id used to identify the student.

      • international

        private boolean international
        international is a Boolean flag to inidcate if the student is an International or Domestic student.

      • internationalStatus

        private java.lang.String internationalStatus
        internationalStatus is an attribute used to indicate if the student is an interantional student, what type of international student they are. Possible values are NONE (not an international student), SHORT_TERM, or SPONSORED.

      • lastName

        private java.lang.String lastName
        The last name of the student. E.g. if the student's name is "John Doe" the last name is "Doe".

      • nationalStudentExchange

        private boolean nationalStudentExchange
        nationalStudentExchange is a Boolean flag indicating if the student is a foreign exchange student.

      • outsideInsurance

        private boolean outsideInsurance
        outsideInsurance is a Boolean flag indicating if the student is covered by separate 3rd party health insurance, and if not that they are required to purchase health insurance through the university.

      • phone

        private java.lang.String phone
        The phone number associated with the student.

      • resident

        private boolean resident
        resident is a Boolean flag used to indicate if the student resides in South Carolina or not. Resident students and non-resident students pay different rates for tuition and therefore this is a key attribute for bill computation.

      • scholarship

        private java.lang.String scholarship
        scholarship is the indicator of which, if any, scholarship the student is entitled to when computing the students bill. The possible valus of scholarship are limited to a known discrete set, e.g. [Athletic, Sims, Woodrow, Departmental, General, None]

      • studyAbroad

        private java.lang.String studyAbroad
        studyAbroad is an indicator to whether the student is studying overseas and if so in what capacity. Values for this field are limited to [REGULAR, COHORT, NONE].

      • termBegan

        private Term termBegan
        The termBegan is the time when the student started college. The value of termBegan is of type Term, e.g. Spring-2017, and will be restricted as such.

      • transactions

        public java.util.List<Transaction> transactions
        transactions is the list of Transaction objects, i.e. payments and amounts, charges and amounts, associated with the student.

      • veteran

        private boolean veteran
        veteran is Boolean flag inidicating if the student is a member of a family of a veteran and therefore entitled to certain reductions in tution.
